            "contentString": "{patientName} has a significant medical history notable for the following conditions and events:\n\n**Smoking History:** 45 pack-year history (smoked approximately 1.5 packs/day from age 24 to age 69). Quit five years ago. This remains his single greatest risk factor for lung malignancy.\n\n**Occupational Exposure:** Worked 35 years in a steel mill with known exposure to industrial dust, fumes, and possible asbestos-containing materials during plant maintenance procedures.\n\n**Chronic Obstructive Pulmonary Disease (COPD):** Diagnosed at age 68 following spirometry demonstrating FEV1/FVC ratio of 0.58. Currently managed with bronchodilators. Hospitalised once in 2019 for an acute COPD exacerbation requiring a short course of systemic corticosteroids.\n\n**Hypertension:** Diagnosed at age 58, currently on antihypertensive therapy.\n\n**Type 2 Diabetes Mellitus:** Diagnosed at age 63, managed with oral agents. HbA1c has been suboptimally controlled (last value 8.1%) due to inconsistent medication adherence and poor dietary compliance.\n\n**Hyperlipidaemia:** Diagnosed at age 60, on statin therapy.\n\n**Benign Prostatic Hyperplasia (BPH):** Diagnosed at age 70, managed with an alpha-blocker.\n\n**Prior Hospitalisations:** One admission for COPD exacerbation (2019); one admission for community-acquired pneumonia (2017) treated with IV antibiotics.\n\n**Surgical History:** Appendectomy at age 22; right inguinal hernia repair at age 55.\n\n**Lifestyle:** Former heavy smoker, occasional alcohol use. Sedentary lifestyle since retirement. Diet is modest and home-cooked but high in simple carbohydrates.\n\n**Immunisations:** Up to date with influenza and pneumococcal vaccines. COVID-19 vaccinated (3 doses).\n\n**Current Oncological Workup:** CT chest revealed a 4.3 cm spiculated mass in the right lower lobe with ipsilateral hilar and mediastinal lymphadenopathy and a moderate right-sided pleural effusion. PET-CT and brain MRI pending. Bronchoscopic biopsy scheduled. Molecular profiling (EGFR, ALK, ROS1, PD-L1) ordered."
